1 (A) (1) IN THIS PART THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (2) (I) “ANCILLARY MEMBER OF THE FRONTLINE TEAM” MEANS AN
4 INDIVIDUAL WHOSE PRIMARY DUTIES INCLUDE SUPPORTING INDIVIDUALS WHO
5 PROVIDE DIRECT PATIENT CARE.
6 (II) “ANCILLARY MEMBER OF THE FRONTLINE TEAM”
7 INCLUDES:
8 1. A DIETARY WORKER;
9 2. A PATIENT CARE TECHNICIAN; AND
10 3. ANY OTHER NONLICENSED STAFF ASSISTING WITH
11 PATIENT CARE.
12 (3) “CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE” MEANS A COMMITTEE
13 ESTABLISHED BY A HOSPITAL IN ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS
14 SECTION.
15 (4) “CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN” MEANS A PLAN DEVELOPED UNDER
16 SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION.
17 (B) THIS PART DOES NOT APPLY TO STATE HOSPITALS.
18 (C) (1) EACH HOSPITAL LICENSED UNDER THIS TITLE SHALL ESTABLISH
19 AND MAINTAIN A CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE THAT HAS EQUAL MEMBERSHIP
20 FROM MANAGEMENT AND EMPLOYEES.
21 (2) EACH CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE ESTABLISHED UNDER
22 THIS PART SHALL INCLUDE AT LEAST ONE OF THE FOLLOWING INDIVIDUALS:
23 (I) A CERTIFIED NURSING ASSISTANT;
24 (II) A DIETARY AIDE;
25 (III) AN EMERGENCY ROOM NURSE;
26 (IV) AN ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICE WORKER;
27 (V) 1. A RESIDENT, IF THE COMMITTEE IS IN A TEACHING
28 HOSPITAL; OR

HOUSE BILL 905 3
1 2. A PHYSICIAN, IF THE COMMITTEE IS IN A HOSPITAL
2 THAT IS NOT A TEACHING HOSPITAL; AND
3 (VI) A TECHNICIAN.
4 (3) A CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE ESTABLISHED UNDER
5 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION MAY INCLUDE A PATIENT ADVOCATE.
6 (D) EACH CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE SHALL DEVELOP A CLINICAL
7 STAFFING PLAN FOR THE HOSPITAL THAT ESTABLISHES THE APPROPRIATE NUMBER
8 OF CLINICIANS NEEDED TO ADMINISTER QUALITY HEALTH CARE BY SETTING.
9 (E) (1) WHEN DEVELOPING A CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN, THE CLINICAL
10 STAFFING COMMITTEE SHALL ESTABLISH, BASED ON THE PATIENT POPULATION OF
11 THE HOSPITAL:
12 (I) SUGGESTED GUIDELINES OR RATIOS, MATRICES, OR GRIDS
13 INDICATING HOW MANY PATIENTS SHOULD BE ASSIGNED TO EACH REGISTERED
14 NURSE BY UNIT OR SETTING; AND
15 (II) THE NUMBER OF REGISTERED NURSES, LICENSED
16 PRACTICAL NURSES, CERTIFIED NURSING ASSISTANTS, CERTIFIED MEDICINE
17 TECHNICIANS, ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICE WORKERS, AND ANCILLARY MEMBERS OF
18 THE DIRECT CARE TEAM THAT SHOULD BE PRESENT ON EACH UNIT DURING EACH
19 SHIFT.
20 (2) TO THE EXTENT PRACTICABLE, THE GUIDELINES ESTABLISHED
21 UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)(I) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE BASED ON NATIONAL
22 EVIDENCE–BASED STANDARDS.
23 (F) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1 EACH YEAR, EACH HOSPITAL, THROUGH THE
24 CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE, SHALL CONDUCT A REVIEW OF THE CLINICAL
25 STAFFING PLAN TO:
26 (1) EVALUATE THE EFFECTIVENESS OF THE CLINICAL STAFFING
27 PLAN DURING THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING YEAR;
28 (2) UPDATE THE CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN TO ENSURE THAT THE
29 CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN CONTINUES TO BE APPROPRIATE AND EFFECTIVE; AND
30 (3) DEVELOP A PROCESS FOR RECEIVING, RESOLVING, AND
31 TRACKING COMPLAINTS RELATED TO THE CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN.

